        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Jan. 31<hi rend="superscript">st</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Dyer</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>In truth I was ashamed of myself, when I saw what trouble I had caused you.— All your information is of the greatest use to me, &amp; I beg of you to thank cordially Prof. Oliver. M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Baker &amp; the others who have aided me.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I can say that I have not asked for information about the plants, in any case, without having spent much time about them.</p>
<p>Cyclamen will be of no use with respect nutation &amp; burying the capsules, but your facts &amp; M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Benthams suggestion about the step in burying shall be worked in in a new Edit. of Forms of Flowers which I must soon prepare.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>The variability of the bloom in the Fern is quite new to me, but I had analogous cases &amp; intended to use the argument about the apparent unimportance of the secretion.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>I will write to Saporta, as Hooker wishes me to do, &amp; will give your general verdict &amp; send the African leaf.—<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>Once again let me thank you very sincerely for all your very valuable information</p>
<p>Yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">a new] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘the next’</note>
